# AI Security Lab – Phase 1 (Local LLM Setup)

## Overview
This project establishes a local AI development environment for experimenting with large language models (LLMs) in a controlled and secure setting. The goal of Phase 1 is to build a foundational lab that will later support AI security testing, including prompt injection, data leakage, and model abuse scenarios.

This lab uses a locally hosted LLM to eliminate external API dependencies and allow safe experimentation with adversarial inputs.

---

## Objectives
- Set up a local AI development environment
- Run a local LLM using Ollama
- Build a Python-based interaction script
- Prepare a reproducible environment for future AI security testing

---

## Tech Stack
- Python
- Ollama (local LLM runtime)
- ChromaDB (vector database - future use)
- VS Code
- Git

